  "text": "Thus, for positive η, the higher order functions vanish for large fields. In [CITATION_1] , one nonGaussian IR-stable fixed point as the supersymmetric analogue of the Wilson-Fisher fixed point has been spotted. It possesses one IR unstable direction defined by w * (0) with critical exponent θ 0 = 1/ν w which can be related to the anomalous dimension η via the superscaling relation 1/ν w = (3 − η)/2 [CITATION_2] .",
